This paper is about improving the performance of a monolingual semantic parser by leveraging data annotated in different languages. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as learning distributed representations and incorporating them as features, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with improving the accuracy of semantic parsing, which is a task related to information retrieval (IR), so it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which are commonly used in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
